commit.message: Merge branch 'bugs/meld-spurious-zero'
In meld, disable logic to detect overlapping index sets of length>1 in symmetry sets; it is incorrect and leads to spurious zeroes.
Update version and changelog.
Merge branch 'cbehan-rev_lookup'
Merge branch 'rev_lookup' of https://github.com/cbehan/cadabra2 into cbehan-rev_lookup
Add debug output.
Turn on LTO for faster linking and to remove a warning.

Consolidate Greek character searches

Searching for keys in a map is just like searching for elements in a set
so we can have everything use the same list of Greek characters.

Signed-off-by: Connor Behan <connor.behan@gmail.com>

Replace Greek letters entered as unicode instead of TeX

People doing quick and dirty things might want to create a new
expression by copying and pasting from the output of a previous
algorithm. The asymmetry here is that input typically has TeX while
output typically has unicode. We can solve this by performing a
replacement in the parser. It is then natural to copy greekmap from
DisplayTerminal to Symbols (and add varphi to it).

In case there are users who input both TeX and unicode and rely on them
being distinct, this could be put behind a command-line argument or
environment variable.

Signed-off-by: Connor Behan <connor.behan@gmail.com>
Tighten conditions on when to accept integer values and sequence values for Indices.

Update Indices documentation

We now mention a list that is not continuous.

Signed-off-by: Connor Behan <connor.behan@gmail.com>

Collect values in a different way

One of the other tests indicates that there actually is supposed to be a
difference between Integer and the values keyword. The latter is needed
to make the evaluate algorithm work. Therefore we should still attempt
to collect values in Indices but failures should not be fatal and
Integer (which we apply no matter what) should do the heavy lifting.

Signed-off-by: Connor Behan <connor.behan@gmail.com>

Add test for the values keyword

The old code with too many checks for a sequence and not enough checks
for a list would both make this fail.

Signed-off-by: Connor Behan <connor.behan@gmail.com>

Only apply Integer to discrete values when safe

This adds an explicit check that there are no gaps.

Signed-off-by: Connor Behan <connor.behan@gmail.com>

Accept all ranges of values for Indices

If a sequence works when passed to Integer, it should also work when it
is the values keyword passed to Indices. The validation code really only
needs to run on expressions that are not sequences.

Signed-off-by: Connor Behan <connor.behan@gmail.com>

Backport pybind11 bugfix (#293)

The last time pybind11 was copied over, it had a small bug which was fixed upstream a month later. This caused cadabra2 to fail with a runtime error when built with -D_GLIBCXX_ASSERTIONS which is the default on some distros.

Backport pybind11 bugfix (#293)

The last time pybind11 was copied over, it had a small bug which was fixed upstream a month later. This caused cadabra2 to fail with a runtime error when built with -D_GLIBCXX_ASSERTIONS which is the default on some distros.

commit.message: Remove duplicate (and outdated) FindPythonLibsNew.cmake.
Fix bug that would incorrectly assume a spinor line in things of the form \psi_a ... \bar{\psi_b}.
Update docs on printing LaTeX expressions. Update changelog.
Bump version.
Add LaTeXString object to wrap strings which should display typeset with LaTeX on capable frontends.
Add another test for the bug fix in the previous commit.
Fix canonicalise not working correctly on objects with Accents.
Catch division by zero when simplifying powers.
Merge branch 'dpbutter-fix-join'
Added test case for fixed join.

Fixed Ex_join to flatten a zero- or one-entry list. This matches
the same behaviour that the original Ex_join had.
Fixed join to avoid crashing on empty lists
Fix Ex slicing error.
Avoid a vector copy in 'join'.
